  <h2 class="melis-section-title">Helping ambitious people <em>win with AI</em>, by treating them as peers — not students.</h2>

  <div class="melis-prose">
    <p>melis.ai is an operator-led education brand. The work is to take what we're learning at the frontier of AI and pass it down — clearly, honestly, without the certainty most teachers perform. We don't promise outcomes. We point at the thing, describe it accurately, and stop talking. The reader is trusted to decide what to do with it.</p>
    <p>Most AI educators are selling certainty in a moment when nobody actually has it. The honest position is that we're all figuring this out — and the difference is whether you're figuring it out by typing prompts in a free chat window or by running a system you've actually built. This brand exists to close that gap. To take the working operation and unbundle it: the principles into essays, the methods into courses, the artefacts into products, the philosophy into a brand book like this one.</p>
    <p>The audience is the person already building something — past the basics, past the hype, ready to do the work. We trust them to keep up. We don't dilute. We don't recap. We treat them as a peer, because they are.</p>
  </div>

  <blockquote class="melis-quote">
    <p>"Technology should make people's lives feel lighter, not heavier. Every visual, verbal, and product decision flows from that."</p>
    <cite>North Star — the test the rest of this document flows from</cite>
  </blockquote>
</section>
